[
  {
    "book": "Obadiah",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "heading",
    "text": "Obadiah 1"
  },
  {
    "book": "Obadiah",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "prose",
    "text": "This is the vision of Obadiah:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Obadiah",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "This is what the Lord GOD says about Edom—"
  },
  {
    "book": "Obadiah",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "We have heard a message from the LORD;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Obadiah",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "an envoy has been sent among the nations"
  },
  {
    "book": "Obadiah",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "to say, “Rise up,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Obadiah",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "and let us go to battle against her!”—"
  },
  {
    "book": "Obadiah",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "“Behold, I will make you small among the nations;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Obadiah",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "you will be deeply despised."
  },
  {
    "book": "Obadiah",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "The pride of your heart has deceived you,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Obadiah",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "O dwellers in the clefts of the rocks"
  },
  {
    "book": "Obadiah",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "whose habitation is the heights,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Obadiah",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "who say in your heart,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Obadiah",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "‘Who can bring me down to the ground?’"
  },
  {
    "book": "Obadiah",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "Though you soar like the eagle"
  },
  {
    "book": "Obadiah",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "and make your nest among the stars,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Obadiah",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "even from there I will bring you down,”"
  },
  {
    "book": "Obadiah",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "declares the LORD."
  },
  {
    "book": "Obadiah",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "“If thieves came to you,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Obadiah",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "if robbers by night—"
  },
  {
    "book": "Obadiah",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "oh, how you will be ruined—"
  },
  {
    "book": "Obadiah",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "would they not steal only what they wanted?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Obadiah",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "If grape gatherers came to you,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Obadiah",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "would they not leave some gleanings?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Obadiah",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "But how Esau will be pillaged,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Obadiah",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "his hidden treasures sought out!"
  },
  {
    "book": "Obadiah",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "All the men allied with you"
  },
  {
    "book": "Obadiah",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "will drive you to the border;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Obadiah",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "the men at peace with you"
  },
  {
    "book": "Obadiah",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "will deceive and overpower you."
  },
  {
    "book": "Obadiah",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "Those who eat your bread"
  },
  {
    "book": "Obadiah",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "will set a trap for you"
  },
  {
    "book": "Obadiah",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "without your awareness of it."
  },
  {
    "book": "Obadiah",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "In that day, declares the LORD,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Obadiah",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "will I not destroy the wise men of Edom"
  },
  {
    "book": "Obadiah",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "and the men of understanding"
  },
  {
    "book": "Obadiah",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "in the mountains of Esau?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Obadiah",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "Then your mighty men, O Teman,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Obadiah",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "will be terrified,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Obadiah",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "so that everyone in the mountains of Esau"
  },
  {
    "book": "Obadiah",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "will be cut down in the slaughter."
  },
  {
    "book": "Obadiah",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "Because of the violence against your brother Jacob,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Obadiah",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "you will be covered with shame"
  },
  {
    "book": "Obadiah",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "and cut off forever."
  },
  {
    "book": "Obadiah",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "On the day you stood aloof"
  },
  {
    "book": "Obadiah",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "while strangers carried off his wealth"
  },
  {
    "book": "Obadiah",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "and foreigners entered his gate"
  },
  {
    "book": "Obadiah",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "and cast lots for Jerusalem,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Obadiah",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "you were just like one of them."
  },
  {
    "book": "Obadiah",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "But you should not gloat in that day,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Obadiah",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "your brother’s day of misfortune,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Obadiah",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "nor rejoice over the people of Judah"
  },
  {
    "book": "Obadiah",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "in the day of their destruction,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Obadiah",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "nor boast proudly"
  },
  {
    "book": "Obadiah",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "in the day of their distress."
  },
  {
    "book": "Obadiah",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "You should not enter the gate of My people"
  },
  {
    "book": "Obadiah",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "in the day of their disaster,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Obadiah",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "nor gloat over their affliction"
  },
  {
    "book": "Obadiah",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "in the day of their disaster,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Obadiah",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "nor loot their wealth"
  },
  {
    "book": "Obadiah",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "in the day of their disaster."
  },
  {
    "book": "Obadiah",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "Nor should you stand at the crossroads"
  },
  {
    "book": "Obadiah",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "to cut off their fugitives,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Obadiah",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "nor deliver up their survivors"
  },
  {
    "book": "Obadiah",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "in the day of their distress."
  },
  {
    "book": "Obadiah",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "For the Day of the LORD is near"
  },
  {
    "book": "Obadiah",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "for all the nations."
  },
  {
    "book": "Obadiah",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "As you have done, it will be done to you;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Obadiah",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "your recompense will return upon your own head."
  },
  {
    "book": "Obadiah",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "For as you drank on My holy mountain,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Obadiah",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "so all the nations will drink continually."
  },
  {
    "book": "Obadiah",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "They will drink and gulp it down;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Obadiah",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "they will be as if they had never existed."
  },
  {
    "book": "Obadiah",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "But on Mount Zion there will be deliverance,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Obadiah",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "and it will be holy,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Obadiah",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "and the house of Jacob"
  },
  {
    "book": "Obadiah",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "will reclaim their possession."
  },
  {
    "book": "Obadiah",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "Then the house of Jacob will be a blazing fire,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Obadiah",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "and the house of Joseph a burning flame;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Obadiah",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "but the house of Esau will be stubble—"
  },
  {
    "book": "Obadiah",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "Jacob will set it ablaze and consume it."
  },
  {
    "book": "Obadiah",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "Therefore no survivor will remain"
  },
  {
    "book": "Obadiah",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "from the house of Esau.”"
  },
  {
    "book": "Obadiah",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "For the LORD has spoken."
  },
  {
    "book": "Obadiah",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "Those from the Negev will possess the mountains of Esau;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Obadiah",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "those from the foothills will possess the land of the Philistines."
  },
  {
    "book": "Obadiah",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "They will occupy the fields of Ephraim and Samaria,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Obadiah",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "and Benjamin will possess Gilead."
  },
  {
    "book": "Obadiah",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "And the exiles of this host of the Israelites"
  },
  {
    "book": "Obadiah",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "will possess the land of the Canaanites as far as Zarephath;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Obadiah",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "and the exiles from Jerusalem who are in Sepharad"
  },
  {
    "book": "Obadiah",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "will possess the cities of the Negev."
  },
  {
    "book": "Obadiah",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "The deliverers will ascend Mount Zion"
  },
  {
    "book": "Obadiah",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "to rule over the mountains of Esau."
  },
  {
    "book": "Obadiah",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "And the kingdom will belong to the LORD."
  }
]